# Twinzy — legacy Cursor shim

This file exists only for legacy Cursor compatibility. The active ruleset is .cursor/rules/*.mdc.
Root CLAUDE.md is the canonical operating policy and always wins.
Precedence: CLAUDE.md > .cursor/rules > AGENTS.md > CODEX.md/cursor.md > this file. Stricter wins.

Compact non-negotiables:
- No any, no eslint-disable, no @ts-ignore/@ts-expect-error, no non-null assertion `!`.
- No TypeScript enum keyword; as-const objects + derived types.
- Zero inline domain definitions: no inline types/interfaces/constants/DTOs/schemas/config maps —
  incl. module-level value consts in layer files (backend architecture/no-inline-domain-definitions;
  frontend frontend-architecture/no-inline-declarations). Definitions live in types/enums/constants/model.
- TSX is pure composition; state/effects/handlers in hooks; logic in modules/<feature> helpers/mappers.
- Components stay small: *.component.tsx / *.container.tsx capped at 130 lines / 60 per function /
  jsx-max-depth (eslint/frontend/component-size.config.mjs); split into sub-components before the cap.
- Backend layers one-way: api -> application -> domain -> infrastructure/adapters; controllers
  delegate exactly one application call per handler.
- Validation is Zod only (zod pipe at the boundary); class-validator is forbidden.
- Vendor ownership: every third-party library wrapped behind an adapter/wrapper; no raw
  SDK/fetch/axios/storage imports in business code (eslint package-boundaries enforced).
- No process.env outside config/bootstrap. Logging via AppLogger (pino) only; never console.*.
- Errors are typed AppError with messageKey errors.<feature>.<key>; never leak stacks/provider errors.
- The game is FREE — no payments, ever.
- No face recognition / identity matching / biometrics / image storage; image goes only to the
  trait-extraction prompt; GEMINI_MODEL from .env; AI outputs Zod-validated + safety-filtered.
- Tests first; coverage on touched modules 95/90/95/95 (stmts/branches/funcs/lines).
- Gates green before done: lint (0/0), typecheck, test:unit, test:coverage, build, security:scan.
- Conventional commits via Husky hooks; never --no-verify; do not commit/push unless asked.
